    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/operating-envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "F1717 compression-bending operating envelope — non-cannulated 7.5 mm construct",
      "description": "Screw outer diameter: 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm. Rod diameter: 5.5 mm ± 0.05 mm. Construct span (vertebral body block centre-to-centre): 44 mm ± 2 mm. Applied compressive load range: 0–2500 N. Bending moment arm (ASTM F1717): 44 mm fixed. Crosshead displacement rate: 5 mm/min (quasi-static). Test temperature: 23 °C ± 2 °C. Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V (ASTM F136) material only. Non-cannulated geometry exclusively; cannulated variants are outside this envelope. Validation experiments sampled at the lower bound (1800 N peak), mid-range (2200 N peak), and upper bound (2500 N peak) of the load envelope to confirm boundary coverage."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability-constraint",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated Ti-6Al-4V 7.5 mm pedicle screw — applicability domain",
      "description": "This UofA applies exclusively to non-cannulated pedicle screws with outer diameter 7.4–7.6 mm manufactured from Ti-6Al-4V per ASTM F136. Constructs must use a 5.5 mm rod and standard polyaxial tulip with set-screw torque 8–12 N·m. The model is not applicable to: (a) cannulated screw variants, (b) screws with outer diameter outside 7.4–7.6 mm, (c) PEEK or CoCr rod materials, (d) dynamic or fatigue loading regimes, or (e) in vivo or cadaveric test conditions."
    }
